### AI-Assisted - Complete Workflow for Aetheric Engine Message Collection
### This file demonstrates the complete workflow from start to finish

### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Step 1: Health Check - Verify the application is running
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 2: Check Initial Status - Should show no messages collected yet
GET {{baseUrl}}/status
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 3: Start Message Collection from Aetheric Engine
### This will:
### - Connect to 35.213.160.152:8080
### - Send AUTH command with JWT token
### - Begin collecting ASCII and binary messages
### - Store messages in Neon PostgreSQL database
### - Stop automatically after 600+ messages
POST {{baseUrl}}/start-collection
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 4: Monitor Collection Progress (run this multiple times)
### Watch the totalMessages count increase towards 600
GET {{baseUrl}}/status
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 5: Wait for Collection to Complete
### The status should show isRunning: false when done
### You can run this periodically to check progress
GET {{baseUrl}}/status
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 6: Validate ASCII Messages
### Verify all ASCII messages were parsed correctly
GET {{baseUrl}}/validation/ascii
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 7: Validate Binary Messages
### Verify all binary messages were parsed correctly
GET {{baseUrl}}/validation/binary
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 8: Get Complete Validation Summary
### Overview of all collected and validated messages
GET {{baseUrl}}/validation/summary
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 9: Get Detailed Validation Report
### Includes sample messages and statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/validation/full-report
Accept: application/json

###

### Optional: Force Stop Collection (if needed during testing)
### Use this only if you need to stop collection before 600 messages
# POST {{baseUrl}}/stop-collection
# Content-Type: application/json

###
